  "body": "Geth version: `1.9.25`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04 in Docker\r\n\r\nCommand line:\r\n````bash\r\ngeth --maxpeers 500 --syncmode full --cache 8192 # + others (data dir, rpc, etc)\r\n````\r\n\r\nMachine:\r\n\r\n- AWS i3.xlarge with NVMe used for chaindata, ext4\r\n- No additional specific configuration\r\n- ipv6 is used and supported\r\n\r\nIssue:\r\nCurrent sync process is terribly slow. I know that this has been reiterated dozens of times, I've looked through all Github tickets and know that IOPS, CPU and RAM requirements are very high (especially former). The only reason I'm posting this once again is that i3.xlarge is very decent machine, and it still only gives me 10 blocks/sec (so I estimate full sync will take like... weeks? months?). Am I missing something?",
