    "body": "EBS is super low on IOPS, don't even bother with that. Attached NVMe is what we use generally for benchmarks (`i3.2xlarge`). It takes us around 8-10 days to do a full sync, though I don't get why you'd want to reexecute all transactions from genesis.\r\n\r\n> BTW, after directly moving chaindata to another place (from EBS to i3 NVMe) and starting geth it has reverted back by 500k blocks.\r\n\r\nYou didn't terminate Geth gracefully. It maintains a large dirty cache in memory that it flushes on shutdown (can take a minute or two). If you hard kill Geth without it flushing it's caches, it will lose all that dirty data and will need to revert to the last block for which it has everything in the database. Please make sure you give Geth 3 minutes to shut down (depends on the amount of ram you permit it to use for caching and the speed at which it can flush to disk).",
