    "body": "Another thing is that during the initial sync you don't want to have that many peers. \r\nManaging these peers will reduce your sync speed. So you would want to run with maybe `--maxpeers 20` until your node is synced and then increase to `--maxpeers 500`. If you want to support the ethereum network, you can also enable `--light.serve 100` to enable one core to serve light clients.\r\n\r\nWill close this issue for now, Feel free to open another one if you found a bug. Generally we prefer that you use the ethereum stackexchange for usage advice",
