    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Well, sorry again for spamming, but looks like I've found the problem.\r\n\r\nSo in my case I've been using Docker with cpu/ram limits. Ram limit was not enough and it has been using swap. While that's already enough for slow performance It has been even worse: due to kernel limitations swap limits didn't propagate to the container so it has been continuously trying to allocate too much memory and dying with OOM that restarted sync over and over doing it slowly due to using swap... Quite challenging. Thanks for your help anyway ",
